<div class="wrap">
  <section class="hero">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1>Why I built this</h1>
    <p class="thesis">My name is <b>Alan Lacroix</b>. I was born in Mexico City and moved to the United States when I was young. I'm building a business in Mexico now and I visit home often, and I realized I'd lost touch with the social, political, and economic reality of the country. So I built this to get it back.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="blk">
    <h2>What it is</h2>
    <p>It starts with as much real-time, first-party data as I can find: the official numbers, straight from the source. Numbers alone don't tell the whole story, so I pair them with the news that gives them context, always tied back to the data. It's the clearest way I've found to see what's actually going on.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="blk">
    <h2>How it started</h2>
    <p>It began as a way for me to stay up to date without wading through a dozen government portals in Spanish. Then family and friends found it useful, so I opened it up. It's free.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="blk">
    <h2>The weekly brief</h2>
    <p>Once a week I write a longer read that pulls together the key areas of interest in Mexico. It works well for investors, executives, or anyone interested in the country and the region. <a class="inline" href="/weekly.html">See what's in it and subscribe &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="blk">
    <h2>A few things I hold to</h2>
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>Every figure links to the source it came from, with the date it was published.</li>
      <li>Mexican official institutions come first — Banxico, INEGI, Hacienda. U.S. agencies, multilateral bodies, polls, and market data are labeled as such, and listed on the <a class="inline" href="/sources.html">Sources</a> page.</li>
      <li>When a feed goes quiet, its last value stays up, marked with the date it stopped.</li>
      <li>The news is here to explain the numbers, not replace them. Nothing here is investment advice, and I have no affiliation with any government or party.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="blk">
    <h2>Tell me what I'm missing</h2>
    <p>I'm open to feedback, and always looking to add new sources, better data feeds, and clearer ways to frame the information. If a number looks wrong or you know a source I should add, please reach out.</p>
    <p>Reach me at <a class="inline" href="mailto:alanlacroix94@gmail.com">alanlacroix94@gmail.com</a>.</p>
  </section>
